Merge

updating the graph model and scoring

Merge pull request #7 from Jorisvansteenbrugge/master

Merged the try catch changes
breadcrump is now able to divide chromosomes into further smaller files based on the users input basesize
added try catch to find the bug
bug fixed where the relative pathing was not maintained after running flatbread
parameter check is more elegant now
fixed a bug where type declaration of gtf files was inconsistant among classes, causing the program to crash
Changed pip install link to the pypi link
numpy has to be installed first
fixed tests to work with db structure
networkx fix, bugfix for BAM files with no reads, version bump

Merge pull request #2 from Jorisvansteenbrugge/master

MaxEnt pathing now derrived from the config file
flatbread does a safe_dump instead of a regular dump now
Changed Prerequisites to the right versions
fixed a syntax error where non default parameter was placed behind a default one
made flatbread a bit more forgiving with yaml configurations
First try to inplement the config maxentpath (not tested yet)
Modded config.py to include the maxent directory from the config yaml file

New working version

Runnable version of changepoint UTR analysis

Checks in case a filtered BAM file is empty

Allow keeping splices from certain annotation sets

option to filter splice junction by evidence and read_count

don't start with empty db by default

threads in both mysql and sqlite
split data loading and model calling

(Hopefully) better way to call best variant

Error if bam file does not exist

Default weight is number of exons
